President Donald J. Trump has declared a major disaster in Puerto Rico and has ordered Federal assistance to support recovery efforts in areas affected by the COVID-19 pandemic. The declaration allows for federal funding to be provided for emergency protective measures and direct assistance to the Commonwealth and eligible local governments. Alexis Amparo has been named as the Federal Coordinating Officer for Federal recovery operations in the affected areas. Further designations may be made if requested by Puerto Rico and deemed necessary based on assessments. For more information, the media can contact the FEMA News Desk.